Task:
Refine the current `/teacher_content` dialog-driven teacher flow so that topic browsing gives better overview without turning the UI back into message clutter.

IMPORTANT:

* This is a focused UI refinement task
* Do NOT redesign the teacher-content dialog architecture
* Do NOT reintroduce multi-message screen clutter
* Do NOT add giant inline button lists for items
* Do NOT redesign asset/domain model
* Audio presence is NOT part of this task
* Only image presence matters for item list markers in this step

Goal:
Improve the current teacher topic flow by adding a human-friendly "show all items" overview and a clearer list+focus browsing experience, while keeping the main teacher dialog compact.

Requirements:

1. Keep the current dialog-driven structure

* `/teacher_content` must remain aiogram-dialog based
* The current main teacher-content screen must remain a single primary screen reused through message editing
* Do NOT regress back into message spraying for the main flow

2. Improve topic item browser overview
   Refine the current topic item browser so the teacher can understand the topic contents faster without opening every item mentally one by one.

Preferred behavior:

* the main topic screen should still show:

  * topic title
  * current item position
  * current selected item details
* additionally, the screen may show a compact visible list window around the current selected item if that improves usability
* keep it compact and readable

3. Add a "Show all" action
   When a topic contains more than 10 items:

* show a dedicated button such as `📄 Show all`
* pressing it sends a separate read-only message with the full list of English item texts in that topic
* this full-list message is intentionally separate from the main dialog screen
* it must not replace the main dialog state
* it must not create a new navigation mode
* it must not contain per-item inline action buttons

4. Full-list message format
   The full-list message should contain:

* topic title
* total item count
* one line per item
* only the English/headword text
* no translations
* no extra fields
* no raw ids

Each item line must show only a simple image-presence marker:

* use one consistent marker for "has image"
* use one consistent marker for "no image"

Do NOT include audio markers in this step.

Choose a clean minimal visual style, for example:

* `🖼 word` for items that have an image
* `• word` for items without an image

or another equally compact readable scheme.
Keep it visually consistent and not noisy.

5. Full-list message behavior

* this message is read-only
* no per-item buttons
* no giant inline keyboard
* ideally only a minimal close/back acknowledgement if really needed, otherwise plain message is acceptable
* do not turn this into a second complex UI flow

6. Threshold behavior

* if topic item count is 10 or fewer, the separate `Show all` button should be hidden
* if topic item count is greater than 10, show it

7. Architecture rules

* keep business logic out of Telegram handlers
* use existing teacher-content domain helpers where possible
* if a new helper is needed for "list all item summaries for topic", keep it focused and small
* do not expand unrelated features
* do not redesign translation handling
* do not redesign media handling
* image presence is determined from the current canonical item asset/media model already present in the project

8. Tests
   Add or update focused tests to cover at least:

* `Show all` button appears only when topic has more than 10 items
* full-list message contains all item headwords
* full-list message uses image-presence marker correctly
* full-list message does not expose ids or extra fields
* main dialog flow remains intact after using `Show all`
* no giant inline keyboard list is introduced

9. Documentation updates
   After implementation, update:

* CHANGELOG.md
* context/current_state.md

Current state must mention:

* teacher topic flow now supports a separate read-only "show all items" message for larger topics
* the full list uses only headwords plus a simple image-presence marker
* audio presence is not shown in that overview
* the main `/teacher_content` dialog remains the primary navigation/editing UI

10. Scope control
    Do NOT:

* add audio markers
* add per-item action buttons to the full-list message
* redesign the whole topic screen from scratch unless minimally needed
* reintroduce multi-message main screen clutter
* add new commands for this feature

